content.description: Runs up the obvious crack on the south side of the boulder. It starts with a high hand jam and a good, finger-size crack under the small overhang. There are decent jams and small crimps the entire way. The crux is keeping enough skin to finish the problem.
content.protection: Bouldering pad recommended and tape comes in handy.
content.location: Problem is in the center of the south face. This boulder can easily be found just south from the Golf Club Boulder.

climbs.name: West Wall
climbs.fa: Someone along time ago I'm sure.

content.description: Sit start with your left hand in an awkward dish and your right on a small crimp.  Climb up to the jugs straight above and top-out via many good edges.  You can down climb to the smaller boulder on the southwest side or use the fallen tree.
content.location: On the west side of the boulder.

content.description:
Start matched on the bad slopey underclings with ok feet. Make a powerful right hand move to a good edge, and hold on tight. Adjust your feet, and make a long move/jump to a decent, left hand gaston over the bulge. From here, match and make your way to the top using some slopers and a good horn near the crack above.

This problem is a bit contrived, since you cannot ever use any holds or feet to the right of the obvious crack going down the center of the boulder. Still, it is a great power problem.
content.location: Go to Cloud Shadow, and hike a minute down to the runners' trail.

climbs.name: Left Bulge Direct
climbs.fa: Christian Griffith and Harrison Dekker, mid '80s

content.description:
This cuts off the awkward and hard start to

Tongue in Cheek

. Start with your left hand on the slopey undercling and your right hand on the horizontal crimp, and chuck your left hand to the lip.  Everything right of the crack is off.

8a.nu concenus
Jump or cheat stone / pad start with right hand on the good crimp and left hand at the the lip.   Then without using the crack, muckle or mantle over.
content.protection: Perfect landing under a small venture, but a pad is nice.

climbs.name: Golum's Delight
climbs.fa: Erik Nickerson, or perhaps some strong 12 year old in the '70s

content.description: Start on top of the 6 foot tall rock just west of the Rear-End Rock.  Climb down through the tunnel and back to the top of the rock.  Both directions go. The ground is off.
content.protection: Tape gloves.  Although this is the ultimate lowball,  a spotter might be nice in case you get stuck in an inverted position.
content.location: This climbs through the tunnel on west side of Rear-End Rock.
